  "title": "The development and exploitation of novel genetic markers in the improvement of chickpea and pigeonpea",
  "abstract": "The chickpea and pigeonpea breeding projects in ICRISAT are aimed at alleviating the constraints to the production of the crops in many regions of Asia and Africa. Production\r\nconstraints for chickpea include: Fusarium wilt, root rot caused by Rhizoctonia spp., Botrytis mould, Ascochyta blight, viruses, Helicoverpa insect, low night temperatures, and drought....",
